caption.p: Trajectories for the infected and fatalities in South Korea due to resusceptibility where it is assumed that 1% of the recovered cases are reinfected after a time span of temporal immunity of (a) 0 day, (b) 30 days, (c) 90 days, and (d) 360 days, respectively. However, these results only apply assuming that if there is no control action being taken to flatten the curve.
